Code of Conduct

Introduction:
Our project community is dedicated to fostering an inclusive and welcoming environment for all participants.
This code of conduct outlines our shared values, expectations for behavior, and guidelines for respectful interaction within our community.
We believe that by treating each other with kindness, respect, and empathy, we can create a positive and collaborative space where everyone feels valued and supported.

Values:
-- Inclusivity: We welcome individuals from all backgrounds, identities, and experiences.
-- Respect: We treat each other with dignity, kindness, and consideration.
-- Open-mindedness: We embrace diverse perspectives and encourage constructive dialogue.
-- Empathy: We seek to understand and support one another with compassion and empathy.
-- Accountability: We hold ourselves and each other accountable for our words and actions.

Collaboration:
We work together collaboratively to achieve our common goals.

Expected Behavior:
-- Being respectful and considerate of others' opinions, backgrounds, and experiences.
-- Avoiding discriminatory language or behavior based on factors like race, gender, sexual orientation, religion, nationality, disability, etc.
-- Providing constructive feedback and criticism in a respectful manner.
-- Resolving conflicts and disagreements professionally and through open communication.

Unacceptable Behavior:
-- Harassment, intimidation, or threats of any kind.
-- Discrimination, including language or actions that perpetuate stereotypes or exclude marginalized groups.
-- Personal attacks, insults, or trolling.
-- Violation of privacy, including sharing personal information without consent.

Reporting Guidelines:
If you experience or witness any behavior that violates this code of conduct, please contact us at tejas.benibagde@gmail.com. You can also report violations anonymously if you prefer. We take all reports seriously and will respond promptly and appropriately.

Enforcement: > Violations of the code of conduct may result in:

    -- Temporary or permanent removal of offending content.
    -- Temporary or permanent bans from participating in the community.
    -- Other actions deemed appropriate by project maintainers to uphold the code of conduct and maintain a positive community environment.

Acknowledgment:
By participating in our project community, you acknowledge your understanding and acceptance of this code of conduct.

Contact Information:
If you have any questions or concerns about this code of conduct or our community guidelines, please contact us at tejas.benibagde@gmail.com.

